{
  "title": "The Rise of Remote Work in 2024",
  "text": "Remote work has become a permanent fixture for many organizations. In a recent survey, 73% of companies said they plan to keep remote or hybrid options permanently. Productivity metrics show a 12% increase on average for remote employees compared to pre‑pandemic levels. Additionally, employee satisfaction rose by 9 points on the standard engagement index. The shift has also impacted real‑estate demand, with office space vacancy rates climbing to 22% in major metros. These trends suggest that remote work is reshaping the modern workplace in profound ways."
}
